title: [Gyldemar Green, Forest]
description: The sound of running water can be heard in the distance as sunlight filters through the trees and is reflected off something to the northeast.  The dulcet voice of a songbird drifts on the wind.

The sound of running water can be heard in the distance as moonlight filters through the trees and is reflected off something to the northeast.  The incessant chirping of a crickets drifts on the wind.
